1
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:37,833
Helsinki, get out of there.
Take shelter in the museum.

2
00:00:37,916 --> 00:00:39,166
I'm making a trench!

3
00:01:13,541 --> 00:01:14,875
Helsinki, do you copy?

4
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:17,833
Helsinki, are you there?

5
00:01:20,458 --> 00:01:21,791
Fatty!

6
00:01:29,166 --> 00:01:31,125
I'm alive.

7
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:34,166
Get out of there now!

8
00:01:40,416 --> 00:01:41,625
Leg trapped.

9
00:01:43,125 --> 00:01:44,375
Open wound.

10
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:46,750
Blood.

11
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:48,666
Lots of blood.

12
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:50,791
Don't fall asleep. We're almost there.

13
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:53,250
I promise you, once we get out of here,

14
00:01:54,125 --> 00:01:56,541
I'm going to show you,
three nights in a row,

15
00:01:56,625 --> 00:01:58,958
why Argentinian meat
is the best in the world.

16
00:01:59,458 --> 00:02:00,583
And then what?

17
00:02:01,458 --> 00:02:03,208
You'll take me to the movies?

18
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:07,791
Yes, but only if you don't fall asleep.
Promise me you'll stay awake.

19
00:02:07,875 --> 00:02:09,166
I'm awake.

20
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:12,500
Squadrons three and nine, now!

21
00:02:12,583 --> 00:02:13,833
Move! Come on!

22
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:18,125
They're here.

23
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:26,583
We don't know what just happened.
It looks like a terrible explosion.

24
00:02:26,666 --> 00:02:29,541
There are hundreds of people
here at the Bank of Spain…

25
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:32,291
LIVE
HEIST AT THE BANK OF SPAIN

26
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:39,083
This is the Professor.
The stormwater tank is safe.

27
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:41,875
I request an assessment
of the situation. Palermo!

28
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:45,291
They blew up the roof! Bogotá,
Rio and I are going to the top floor.

29
00:02:45,875 --> 00:02:47,416
Helsinki's trapped.

30
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:49,041
Lisbon, location.

31
00:02:49,958 --> 00:02:51,666
Second floor, with Stockholm.

32
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,833
Tokyo, location.

33
00:02:53,625 --> 00:02:57,000
About to go out onto the roof.
We'll attack them from behind.

34
00:02:57,083 --> 00:02:59,000
-No, don't open that door!
-What?

35
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:01,125
-And Helsinki?
-They'll kill you.

36
00:03:01,208 --> 00:03:02,416
They're coming down!

37
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:08,250
Cover the flanks and stay together.

38
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,375
If you don't go, they'll kill Helsinki.

39
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:13,291
Go!

40
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:15,458
Should we go out or not?

41
00:03:15,541 --> 00:03:19,000
There are 100 snipers aiming
at the roof, and they're soldiers.

42
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:21,666
They won't let you attack
from behind. They'll blow your heads off.

43
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:25,041
Professor, you're sacrificing a man!

44
00:03:25,125 --> 00:03:28,041
The only way to save him
is to attack on two flanks.

45
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,125
We'll use the hole in the roof.

46
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:33,166
But you have to get out there
without getting killed, and I know how.

47
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,500
Go get the hostages.

48
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:42,791
Maintain your position!

49
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,000
Fire at three o'clock!

50
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:07,666
Come on!

51
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,250
Gandía!

52
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:16,458
Come on!

53
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:18,291
Take cover! Quick!

54
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:20,375
Now!

55
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:27,333
Everyone take cover!

56
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:59,541
We'd often thought we were at war.

57
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:04,416
But that was simply because

58
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:07,000
we didn't know what war actually was.

59
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,500
Frederiksborg Castle.

60
00:06:16,583 --> 00:06:19,083
It has tight security measures.

61
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:22,958
Just to get in or out, you must go through
two arches with metal detectors

62
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:25,791
and armed security guards.

63
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:28,541
All that's before you reach the party.

64
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:30,708
It'll be the perfect soiree.

65
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:33,208
Fancy cars, tuxedos,

66
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:36,291
cocktails, classical music
and 12 kilos of gold.

67
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,416
Tatiana's fingers will work their magic.

68
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,041
And all we have to do is enjoy the party.

69
00:06:44,166 --> 00:06:49,166
Why? By then, the trickiest part
of the job will have been taken care of.

70
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,500
In fact, you'll have done it
the day before.

71
00:06:52,375 --> 00:06:54,041
-Me?
-Yes, you.

72
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:57,958
You're the only one among us
with the plain, inconspicuous appearance

73
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,291
of a piano tuner.

74
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:05,541
What's this?

75
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:06,458
Well,

76
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:11,250
it's a magnetic stripe card reader,
a skimmer for cloning cards.

77
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,916
Exactly!

78
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,333
