card information at ATMs and all that.

80
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:23,666
Tatiana will suddenly feel indisposed.

81
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,166
Nerves, the concert…

82
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:26,375
I need some air.

83
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:30,458
So you'll be left on your own
with a magnificent grand piano.

84
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:33,041
You'll need help.

85
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:40,083
This type of magnetic stripe card cloner

86
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:42,500
requires you to be within ten centimeters

87
00:07:42,583 --> 00:07:44,541
of the card you want to clone

88
00:07:44,625 --> 00:07:46,500
for 30 seconds, obviously.

89
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,791
That's easy,
they'll be hanging from their necks.

90
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:54,541
Nothing a stubborn B-flat can't fix.

91
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:03,958
Then your tool cart comes into play.

92
00:08:04,458 --> 00:08:07,208
That's where we'll hide the fake pieces.

93
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:11,250
It's coated with barium sulfate,

94
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,916
so an X-ray machine won't detect anything.

95
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,500
They'll escort you to the safe place
where the pieces will be kept.

96
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:31,583
From then on,
Hans will be the only problem.

97
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:34,500
-Hans?
-The security guard at the gold room.

98
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,500
He's always by the door.

99
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:38,333
He never leaves.

100
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:41,083
This man has no wife,

101
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:44,458
no dog, no kids,

102
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:47,833
and his father is senile.
What's his weak spot?

103
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:52,250
I don't know. A second-degree relative?

104
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,875
Why resort to a second-degree relative?
His father is senile.

105
00:08:55,958 --> 00:08:56,958
His father.

106
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:58,125
His father's senile.

107
00:08:58,208 --> 00:09:00,708
He's in a sanitarium.
He doesn't recognize anyone anymore.

108
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:21,958
-Bring in Cristoff.
-Copy that.

109
00:09:29,541 --> 00:09:30,458
Rafael.

110
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,166
The briefcase.

111
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:54,541
Thank you.

112
00:09:55,666 --> 00:09:56,583
We're in.

113
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:19,958
Set Cristoff free.

114
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,958
Walk towards the music, Cristoff.

115
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,375
Towards the music.

116
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,125
Cristoff is on the move.

117
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:36,541
-Cameras?
-I'm accessing the system.

118
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:38,666
Music.

119
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:41,291
Music.

120
00:10:44,416 --> 00:10:45,541
I got it.

121
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:46,750
It's on a loop.

122
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,125
Music.

123
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:52,500
Picture Hans's astonishment.

124
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:55,291
He thinks his father is in a sanitarium,

125
00:10:55,916 --> 00:10:58,458
in slippers, watching Wheel of Fortune,

126
00:10:58,541 --> 00:10:59,791
and all of a sudden…

127
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:03,666
Music.

128
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:06,166
Music.

129
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:10,708
This is Bear 3. Emergency in Room 1.
I need an immediate replacement in Room 1.

130
00:11:11,791 --> 00:11:12,708
Copy that, Bear 3.

131
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,041
On my way.

132
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,416
Rock and roll.

133
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:46,625
There's something I haven't told you.

134
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:48,708
I have absolutely no idea

135
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,625
what's in there.

136
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,583
Music.

137
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:02,833
You never know
what you'll find in a secret vault.

138
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:21,750
It's beautiful.

139
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:29,708
Let's do it.

140
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:32,500
They're encrypted safe-deposit boxes.

141
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,958
Excuse me.

142
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:42,708
And that is the key
that opens all the doors.

143
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:45,125
Good. Which box contains the gold?

144
00:12:45,208 --> 00:12:49,041
The information is in here.
It's a matter of coding. I can hack it.

145
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:58,166
This box is attached to a beam.
It's a fixed structure.

146
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,416
Because the walls move.

147
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,666
This is the most fascinating
security system I've ever seen.

148
00:13:10,708 --> 00:13:12,583
He just found his father.

149
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:16,333
Don't grow too fond of it, son.
You've got one minute to blow it up.

150
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:19,166
I can't do this in one minute, Dad.

151
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:22,791
Jakov, it's an emergency.

152
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:24,583
We need three minutes.

153
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:30,708
-I can't do it in three minutes either.
-It's okay, don't worry.

154
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:33,791
You'll have plenty of time
to figure it out in jail.

155
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:37,125
Excuse me.

156
00:13:37,916 --> 00:13:40,375
I'm a doctor.
I think this gentleman doesn't feel well.

157
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:43,250
He's disoriented.
It's nothing serious. Thanks.

158
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:44,708
Come on, Dad.

159
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:47,958
-Come on!
-I found the gold. I'm breaking the code.

160
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:49,875
-How much longer?
-I don't know.

161
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:52,708
Jakov.

162
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:54,833
Two minutes.

163
00:13:58,666 --> 00:13:59,666
Got it!

164
00:14:25,208 --> 00:14:26,791
Excuse me.

165
00:14:26,875 --> 00:14:28,375
Out there…

166
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:30,500
One minute, Jakov.

167
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:34,958
He crossed the line with some ladies.

168
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:36,500
What?

169
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:41,583
The president of the foundation
almost called the police.

170
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:44,583
What did he do?

171
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:47,083
He said

172
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:49,541
inappropriate things.

173
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:50,541
What things?

174
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:55,000
About…

175
00:14:56,916 --> 00:14:58,250
genitals.

176
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:08,458
Did you see if he was with someone
or how he got here?

177
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:10,625
Move aside.

178
00:15:11,666 --> 00:15:12,500
Come on, Dad.

179
00:15:13,541 --> 00:15:15,875
Andrés, Hans is suspicious.

180
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:17,166
They're headed your way.

181
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:25,166
Excuse me.

182
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:33,125
Jakov, it's done.

183
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:57,250
We're out.

184
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:16,750
The adrenaline,

185
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:18,583
the endorphins…

186
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:30,416
You feel powerful. Don't you, son?

187
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:49,458
It's amazing.

188
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:53,500
The most important lesson comes now.

189
00:16:56,708 --> 00:16:58,166
That's it.

190
00:17:03,416 --> 00:17:05,208
What are you doing? No.

191
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:06,750
Dad?

192
00:17:09,541 --> 00:17:10,375
Dad!

193
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:19,166
-Why?
-I'm teaching you a lesson!

194
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:21,541
A lesson? I can't believe this.

195
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:25,750
You just threw away 12 kilos of gold.
That's 15 million euros.

196
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:28,750
Teach me a lesson, my ass.

197
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:30,375
Look at you.

198
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:36,750
Only a thief can feel
that something they don't own is theirs.

199
00:17:39,166 --> 00:17:40,750
Now you know you're one of us.

200
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,791
So, next time,

201
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:49,541
leave that arrogance
and moral superiority behind

202
00:17:49,625 --> 00:17:53,166
and don't you ever
call your father a cynic again.

203
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:57,041
Now it's time to enjoy ourselves.

204
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:59,791
I came here to listen to Tatiana play.

205
00:18:07,375 --> 00:18:08,708
Bravo!

206
00:18:10,041 --> 00:18:12,083
The dream of any thief is

207
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:15,125
to leave the place of the heist
surrounded by applause,

208
00:18:15,208 --> 00:18:19,125
people taking pictures, smiling,

209
00:18:19,875 --> 00:18:22,125
calm, determined

210
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,291
and in love.

211
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:32,458
And, above all,

212
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,500
free of any suspicion.

213
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:40,083
We'll leave the country undetected,

214
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:43,541
in a beautiful, small boat,
celebrating Tatiana's success,

215
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:45,333
headed to Malmö, Sweden.

216
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:46,958
What's wrong with him?

217
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:49,333
A tantrum.

218
00:18:49,875 --> 00:18:52,833
I never know
whether he's tired, hungry or gassy.

219
00:18:58,541 --> 00:19:00,375
My love, are you ready?

220
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:01,708
Of course.

221
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:33,083
Let's have a look!

222
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,083
You expected us
to walk out the door with it?

223
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:01,083
I never took you to play tennis.

224
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:07,708
We never cycled up
a mountain pass together or went rowing.

225
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:12,458
You wouldn't have learned anything new
from doing that with your father.

226
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:15,375
But here, you will.

227
00:20:21,416 --> 00:20:23,666
If you really want something in life,

228
00:20:25,125 --> 00:20:27,416
you have to steal it from whomever has it.

229
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,708
That's how the world works, my son.

230
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:00,541
Now!

231
00:21:08,208 --> 00:21:09,791
We're here, Fatty. Don't worry.

232
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:14,083
Stay calm, Fatty. I'm here.

233
00:21:27,958 --> 00:21:28,958
Arteche.

234
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:30,166
Arteche!

235
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:33,166
I can't hear anything. Tosco's injured.

236
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:37,291
His pulse is very weak.

237
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:43,500
It hit the femoral artery.

238
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,833
We gotta make a fucking tourniquet.

239
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:49,583
Breathe, Fatty.
We'll get you out of here, you hear me?

240
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,958
Put it higher. Higher. Come on.

241
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:56,375
Sagasta, do you copy?

242
00:21:56,458 --> 00:22:01,000
-What the hell is going on?
-It was a hostile rocket.

243
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:02,708
I want a damage report now!

244
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:05,833
Shut your fucking mouth, Colonel.
I have wounded men in here.

245
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:09,166
Canalejas, we have to make
a trench to secure the perimeter--

246
00:22:15,291 --> 00:22:16,583
Hey, look at me.

247
00:22:16,666 --> 00:22:18,625
This is going to hurt. Ready?

248
00:22:19,125 --> 00:22:20,625
Three, two, one.

249
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:25,750
Get the bomb disposal robot.
Any second now, we'll go in from below.

250
00:22:28,875 --> 00:22:30,208
We're going up!

251
00:22:30,291 --> 00:22:33,500
It's your lucky day.
We're running a drill, like in school.

252
00:22:33,583 --> 00:22:35,375
So keep quiet and get in line.

253
00:22:35,458 --> 00:22:37,250
You're the infantry now.

254
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:40,833
Matías, the backpacks with the equipment.
We're going to the roof.

255
00:22:40,916 --> 00:22:41,750
Copy that.

256
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:46,625
Come on, move!

257
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,291
Palermo, cut my fucking leg off.

258
00:22:54,375 --> 00:22:55,208
Cut it off.

259
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:57,000
Look at me.

260
00:22:57,708 --> 00:23:00,583
I won't cut your leg off,
you hear me? I won't.

261
00:23:00,666 --> 00:23:01,916
Palermo,

262
00:23:02,416 --> 00:23:05,041
my femur, tibia and knee are shattered.

263
00:23:05,916 --> 00:23:07,166
Everything.

264
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:13,333
They'll cut it off in the hospital.
You know damn well, Palermo.

265
