525
00:42:12,916 --> 00:42:13,750
I think…

526
00:42:16,041 --> 00:42:19,875
that you keep living
in the last thought you have before dying.

527
00:42:23,083 --> 00:42:26,125
That's why, when things get crazy,
I think of when I was happy.

528
00:42:28,083 --> 00:42:29,625
And in those memories,

529
00:42:31,416 --> 00:42:33,416
I'll stay and live forever.

530
00:42:38,208 --> 00:42:39,541
That's a great plan.

531
00:42:46,875 --> 00:42:49,875
-What? Who's next door?
-Come on. Who do you think?

532
00:42:49,958 --> 00:42:51,166
-No.
-Of course!

533
00:42:51,250 --> 00:42:53,541
Yeah, Aikido, Professor!

534
00:42:53,625 --> 00:42:55,500
Aikido all the way, man!

535
00:42:55,583 --> 00:42:57,041
Shut up!

536
00:43:04,416 --> 00:43:05,666
Who's in charge here?

537
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:07,416
Major Sagasta.

538
00:43:07,500 --> 00:43:09,333
Sagasta, you're surrounded.

539
00:43:10,333 --> 00:43:12,791
Throw your weapons
into the middle of the room, now.

540
00:43:12,875 --> 00:43:15,541
Come and get them, pillow-biter!

541
00:43:15,625 --> 00:43:17,416
Sagasta, update.

542
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:20,416
Send in the second detachment.
The whole gang is here.

543
00:43:20,500 --> 00:43:23,791
Even the postman and his mom
could walk in the main door right now.

544
00:43:24,291 --> 00:43:25,958
Sagasta, you have to resist.

545
00:43:31,375 --> 00:43:33,041
There won't be a second detachment.

546
00:43:33,875 --> 00:43:37,375
They snuck in right under your nose
and now you leave us high and dry.

547
00:43:39,708 --> 00:43:40,791
Over and out.

548
00:43:48,083 --> 00:43:49,750
Arteche, what do you think?

549
00:43:49,833 --> 00:43:53,000
We're between two fronts.
We need to get rid of one.

550
00:43:57,583 --> 00:43:59,666
Sagasta, you've got ten seconds.

551
00:44:00,458 --> 00:44:03,125
Gandía, can you activate
the museum's security lock?

552
00:44:03,208 --> 00:44:06,250
Affirmative.
There's a fingerprint reader in the room.

553
00:44:06,333 --> 00:44:07,416
Seven seconds!

554
00:44:10,541 --> 00:44:14,083
Okay, four corners. Wait for my order.

555
00:44:19,333 --> 00:44:20,750
Five seconds!

556
00:44:23,791 --> 00:44:24,791
Four!

557
00:44:28,375 --> 00:44:29,625
Three!

558
00:44:31,208 --> 00:44:32,375
Two!

559
00:44:33,041 --> 00:44:36,500
All right! We'll drop our weapons.

560
00:44:36,583 --> 00:44:40,000
Hands on your heads!
Get down on the ground, damn it!

561
00:44:40,083 --> 00:44:41,166
Okay.

562
00:44:44,041 --> 00:44:45,958
We're going to drop our weapons.

563
00:44:49,083 --> 00:44:50,666
I don't like this one bit.

564
00:44:50,750 --> 00:44:52,041
Now!

565
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:54,083
Grenade!

566
00:44:57,458 --> 00:44:58,583
Get back!

567
00:45:17,375 --> 00:45:18,333
Fuck!

568
00:45:28,125 --> 00:45:30,375
-What's happening, Lisbon?
-Grenades!

569
00:45:30,458 --> 00:45:33,833
-We've retreated to the museum.
-Don't lose sight of Tokyo's group.

570
00:45:40,625 --> 00:45:42,166
Tokyo, keep going!

571
00:45:44,833 --> 00:45:45,708
Impossible.

572
00:45:45,791 --> 00:45:46,833
I have no visual.

573
00:46:07,583 --> 00:46:10,083
They're lowering the doors.
There's a security lock.

574
00:46:10,166 --> 00:46:11,375
A security lock?

575
00:46:12,500 --> 00:46:14,375
That's impossible. It's not in the plans.

576
00:46:14,458 --> 00:46:16,541
They must have installed them afterwards

577
00:46:16,625 --> 00:46:19,166
'cause three doors are closing, Professor.

578
00:46:24,291 --> 00:46:26,333
Come on!

579
00:46:41,541 --> 00:46:42,750
Go to the kitchen.

580
00:47:29,416 --> 00:47:31,916
Tokyo!

581
00:47:34,125 --> 00:47:36,541
A little bird just told me Nairobi

582
00:47:36,625 --> 00:47:43,000
is saving you a place in heaven.

583
00:49:21,583 --> 00:49:24,125
Subtitle translation by: Molly Yurick

